  "prompt": "What is the best site to download songs?",
  "response": "The best site to download songs legally depends on your preferences and location. Here are some popular and reputable options:\n\n### **1. Paid Platforms (Legal Download)**\n- **iTunes Store:** One of the most popular platforms for purchasing and downloading songs, available on Apple devices.\n- **Amazon Music:** Offers a vast library of songs for purchase and download.\n- **Bandcamp:** Great for independent artists; you can buy music directly from them.\n- **Google Play Music (now merged with YouTube Music):** Allows you to purchase and download songs.\n- **Qobuz:** Known for high-quality audio downloads, popular among audiophiles.\n\n### **2. Streaming Platforms (Legal Download for Offline Use)**\n- **Spotify:** Premium users can download songs for offline listening.\n- **Apple Music:** Allows downloads for offline playback with a subscription.\n- **YouTube Music:** Premium users can download songs and videos.\n- **Tidal:** Offers high-fidelity music downloads for offline listening.\n\n### **3. Free and Legal Platforms**\n- **Free Music Archive (FMA):** Offers a mix of free-to-download music, often licensed under Creative Commons.\n- **Jamendo:** Focuses on independent artists and offers free downloads for personal use.\n- **SoundCloud:** Some artists allow free downloads of their tracks; look for the \"Download\" button.\n\n### **Important Notes**\n- **Avoid illegal sites:** Downloading from unauthorized platforms like torrent sites is illegal and can expose you to malware.\n- **Check licensing:** Even on free platforms, ensure the music is licensed for download and use.\n- **Support artists:** Whenever possible, purchase or stream music through official channels to support creators.",
